abstract: A suit against New York City and some of its officials that charged they had deliberately misled buyers of city securities during the worst of the fiscal crisis was dismissed by a Federal judge yesterday.
headline_main: Investors' Suit Against City Dismissed; Cases Were Consolidated Records Called Falsified

abstract: WASHINGTON, Jan. 27 When President Carter's Cabinet secretaries met at the White House for a preview of the Federal budget that is to be submitted to Congress tomorrow, James T. McIntyre Jr., director of the Office of Management and Budget, informed them in somber tones that Mr. Carter had decided at the last  minute to cut spending by a staggering $100 billion. The secretaries stared in disbelief.
headline_main: With New Budget, Due Today, McIntyre Gains as a Carter Aide; Craftsman for Cornerstone With Budget Due Today, McIntyre Gains as Carter's Aide Successor to Lance

abstract: Two American reporters and an editor borrowed an outdated border pass from a French journalist and managed earlier this month to cross the Thai border into Cambodia to visit a refugee camp.
